\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {22}{\ignorespaces Per-task adapter sanity-check outcomes for each streaming baseline. Both adapters drive the browser and emit valid tool calls (\texttt  {click}, \texttt  {fill}, \texttt  {type\_text}) on every task; every attempted action lands on the DOM. Both score 0/5 task-correct because the models choose the wrong target (e.g., F-E2 cookies dismissed instead of accepted), hallucinate content (C-E1 typed a URL not present in the recording), or commit prematurely (I-E1 typed before reading the page). The same failure modes appear on the audio subset (Table\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:streaming}), confirming the audio-subset failures are content-driven rather than infrastructural.\relax }}{34}{table.caption.31}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:streaming_sanity_detail}{{22}{34}{Per-task adapter sanity-check outcomes for each streaming baseline. Both adapters drive the browser and emit valid tool calls (\texttt {click}, \texttt {fill}, \texttt {type\_text}) on every task; every attempted action lands on the DOM. Both score 0/5 task-correct because the models choose the wrong target (e.g., F-E2 cookies dismissed instead of accepted), hallucinate content (C-E1 typed a URL not present in the recording), or commit prematurely (I-E1 typed before reading the page). The same failure modes appear on the audio subset (Table~\ref {tab:streaming}), confirming the audio-subset failures are content-driven rather than infrastructural.\relax }{table.caption.31}{}}
